Column Comment.0: COORDINATE SYSTEM ID: unique identifier for the coordinate system.
Column Comment.1: ACTIVE INDICATOR: A Y/N flag indicating whether this row of data is currently eitheractive / valid (Y) or inactive / invalid (N).
Column Comment.2: COORDINATE SYSTEM TYPE: the type of coordinate system. Will includeGeographic coordinate system, local spatial coordinate system, Geocentriccoordinate system, Map Grid coordinate system, and vertical coordinate system.Geocentric is typically not used and it is strongly recommended not to use verticalcoordinate systems, as the model is not complete in this area.
Column Comment.3: COORD SYSTEM ABBREVIATION: common abbreviation for the coordinate system.
Column Comment.4: COORDINATE SYSTEM AREA: name of the area over which the coordinate systemis valid.
Column Comment.5: COORDINATE SYSTEM NAME: The name of the coordinate system.
Column Comment.6: COORDINATE SYSTEM SHORT NAME: short name for the coordinate system.
Column Comment.7: COORDINATE SYSTEM UNITS OF MEASURE: The unit of measure associated withthis coordinate system (i.e. meters for UTM, decimal degrees for WGS 84)
Column Comment.8: DATUM ORGINAL UNIT OF MEASURE: DATUM_OUOM needs to be kept to trackspecial units of measure (such as the Chinese Li). Do not delete this column.
Column Comment.9: EFFECTIVE DATE: The date that the data in this row first came into effect.
Column Comment.10: EXPIRY DATE: The date that the data in this row was no longer active or in effect.
Column Comment.11: GEODETIC DATUM IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the geodetic datum.
Column Comment.12: N VALUE: Difference in elevation between the ellipsoid and the geoid at themonument at which the datum is defined.
Column Comment.13: N VALUE OUOM: Original units of measure for N value
Column Comment.14: OWNER BUSINESS ASSOCIATE IDENTIFIER: Unique identifier for the businessassociate who is the owner or custodian of this coordinate system. Often agovernment or regulatory agency, but can be private companies or even individuals.
Column Comment.15: COORDINATE SYSTEM ID: unique identifier for the coordinate system.
Column Comment.16: PERSPECTIVE HEIGHT: Associated with LanSat projections.
Column Comment.17: ROW_MANAGEMENT_GUID: This value may be used to provide a global uniqueidentifier for this row of data. Use of this column is not mandatory, but if used,optional PPDM NOT NULL and UNIQUE INDEX constraints provided in the datamodel DDL should becreated.
Column Comment.18: PRIME MERIDIAN IDENTIFER: Unique identifier for the Prime Meridian.
Column Comment.19: PRINICPAL MERIDIAN CODE: A reference table identifying the valid principalmeridians used for legal survey descriptions. This is the f irst meridian in the surveyfrom which all other meridians are numbere d. For example Black Hi lls 1878, Boise1867, Chicksaw 1833, ...
Column Comment.20: PROJECTION TYPE: A reference table identifying valid classifications of projectionsused by individual map projections. For example, Mercator, Lambert, Polyconic, ...
Column Comment.21: REFERENCE ELEVATION: The height above mean sea level for the location thatdefines the Vertical Datum.
Column Comment.22: REFERENCE ELEVATION OUOM: The original UOM for the Reference Elevation.
Column Comment.23: REMARK: Narrative remarks about this row of data.
Column Comment.24: GRID SYSTEM ROTATION INDICATOR: Indicates whether this map grid system isrotated from another map grid system.
Column Comment.25: SOURCE: The individual, company, state, or government agency designated as thesource of information for this row.
Column Comment.26: SOURCE DOCUMENT: A list of documents that are used as the source for supplyingdata. Source documents may include government and regulatory forms, operatorreports or scout tickets, publications, news letters, books or jounals.
Column Comment.27: VERTICAL DATUM TYPE: The types of vertical datum. For example, geoidal heightthe height above the geoid, elevation the height above mean sea level...
Column Comment.28: ROW CHANGED BY: Application login id of the user who last changed the row.
Column Comment.29: ROW CHANGED DATE: System date of the last time the row was changed.
Column Comment.30: ROW CREATED BY: System user who created this row of data.
Column Comment.31: ROW CREATED DATE: Date that the row was created on.
Column Comment.32: ROW_EFFECTIVE_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of datais effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row of data wasmade available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.33: ROW_EXPIRY_DATE: A system assigned date that specified when a row of data isno longer effective from a systems perspective. This may be the date that a row ofdata was no longer available to end users, for example.
Column Comment.34: PPDM ROW QUALITY: A set of values indicating the quality of data in this row,usually with reference to the method or procedures used to load the data, althoughother types of quality reference are permitted.
